{"id": 232008476, "title": "Brantford mom in shock after winning $150,000", "text": "Jodie McLean got her first big win on a The Bigger Spin Instant game. \u201cI went to check my ticket after an appointment and the lottery terminal froze,\u201d McLean said while visiting the OLG Prize Centre to collect her winnings. \u201cThe retailer said I won $150. I was shocked when I realized I had actually won $150,000. I couldn\u2019t believe it.\u201d McLean said she wanted to tell her daughter first but was so nervous she kept dialing the wrong number. \u201cShe couldn\u2019t believe it either. \u201cI was screaming and crying. I was thinking \u2018Is this really happening to me?\u2019 I was so happy.\u201d McLean said she plans to buy a car, take a trip and share some winnings with her children. The winning ticket was purchased at Telly\u2019s Variety on Colborne Street. The game McLean played is a $10 ticket that combines scratch play with prizes revealed in-store by an animated spinning wheel on a lottery terminal screen. Players who get \u201cBigger Spin\u201d at the store, can spin the big wheel at the OLG Prize Centre where they are guaranteed a prize of $500,000 to $1 million. SGamble@postmedia.com @EXPSGamble", "summary": "A Brantford mom of six has won $150,000 after playing the lottery for more than a decade. Jodie McLean got her first big win on a The Bigger Spin Instant game. &#8220;I went to check my ticket after an appointment and the lottery terminal froze,&#8221; McLean said while visiting the OLG Prize Centre to collect [&#8230;]", "url": "https://www.parisstaronline.com/news/local-news/brantford-mom-in-shock-after-winning-150000/wcm/990e32a2-037d-432b-b6d5-b7cbdb10818d", "image": "https://smartcdn.gprod.postmedia.digital/nexus/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/br-0606-br-lotterywin-2.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-09 14:33:33", "author": "Susan Gamble", "authors": ["Susan Gamble"], "language": "en", "source_country": "ca", "sentiment": -0.217}